Egg Lemon Chicken Soup

32 ounces chicken broth
½ cup rice
2 beaten eggs
1/3 cup fresh squeezed lemon juice
1 ½ to 2 cups shredded cooked chicken

Bring broth to a boil, add rice; boil until the rice is tender (15 to 20 minutes).

Beat eggs. Slowly add lemon juice to eggs as you beat them vigorously.

Then very slowly add broth to the egg-lemon mixture n little at a time.

Add chicken.  Serve


